# github-actions-ci-patterns — History

## v2.2.0 (2026-04-25)

**Changed by:** ProjectKeystone PR #451 — aligning GitHub Actions workflow job names to branch protection required status check contexts
**Verification:** verified-local

### What changed
- Added Step 12: Required Check Alignment — audit command, explicit `name:` field pattern, orphan workflow deletion, duplicate job removal, landing order rule
- Added 3 new Failed Attempts rows (implicit job ID match, orphan workflow kept "just in case", duplicate CodeQL job)
- Added 4 new When to Use trigger conditions (required checks mismatch, orphan workflows, duplicate checks, uncoordinated workflow landing)
- Added 3 new Quick Reference table rows (permanently blocked PRs, orphan workflow fix, duplicate job fix)
- Updated description to include required check alignment use case
- Updated tags to include branch-protection, required-checks, status-checks
- Bumped version 2.1.0 → 2.2.0, updated date to 2026-04-25

### Why
PR #451 on HomericIntelligence/ProjectKeystone revealed three related CI hygiene problems: (1) five security-scan.yml jobs had no explicit `name:` field — their IDs matched required check contexts only by coincidence; (2) `_required.yml` ran on every push/PR but none of its jobs were in the required checks list — pure runner waste; (3) `security-scan.yml` duplicated the CodeQL job from `codeql-analysis.yml`, burning 20 runner minutes per PR for a check that wasn't even required.

### Previous version (v2.1.0) snapshot

The v2.1.0 content is preserved in git history at the commit immediately preceding this amendment.

